voice_to_text: The lady of the house sampled her dinner while the maid beside her stood motionless, trembling beneath the table. Her entire family hid in silence. By luck, when dinner was over and the lady went upstairs, the maid whispered frantically for her family to crawl out and escape. Just then, the homeowner's young daughter appeared at the foot of the stairs. She wasn't suspicious. She simply wanted to pitch a tent on the front lawn for the night. In that instant, the hidden family slipped under the sofa, their hearts pounding as the wealthy family lingered nearby. The night stretched endlessly. The little girl played outside in her cozy tent while her parents relaxed on the living room couch. Beneath them, the poor family lay perfectly still, barely daring to breathe. Only when the couple finally drifted into sleep did they slide out from beneath the sofa, tiptoeing toward the garage and vanishing quietly through the villa's back door. There's an old saying, a storm always exposes the distance between classes. The rich live above the flood, while the poor are swept downhill, carried away like fragments of a broken world. When the family returned home, the devastation was beyond belief. Their basement shelter was gone, water up to their waists, filth gushing endlessly from the toilet. Yet outside the mansion, the child's small tent remained untouched, dry, as if blessed by invisible fortune. Staring at the ruins, the eldest son made a silent vow, one day, no matter the Cost. He would climb his way into that upper world and give his family the life they had only dreamed of.

voice_to_text: What last meal did you order on death row that saved your life? I wrote out my last meal request on Wednesday, 47 ingredients, every measurement and technique precise. My mother's meatloaf recipe from memory. The guard took the form and left. An hour later, the prison chef showed up at my cell. You, Preston? Yeah. What is this? He asked, holding up my form. Meatloaf. This is a novel, not a recipe. Ground beef, 60% ground pork, 40%. Bread crumbs soaked in whole milk for exactly 10 minutes. Three eggs beaten until frothy. Yellow onion, not white, sauteed in butter until translucent. Ash time, not dried. Worcestershire, 2 tablespoons, no substitutes. Tomato paste, garlic pressed, not minced. Paprika, black pepper, sea salt, not table salt. And this glaze, half cup ketchup, brown sugar, apple cider vinegar, mustard powder. Brush on at 340 degrees. Twenty minutes before done, he looked at me through the bars. Why so specific how my mother made it. Your mother was a chef? No, just a mom who made meatloaf every birthday. Some of these ingredients we don't stock. Fresh thyme, whole milk, real butter. We'll have to special order them. I have 48 hours, he sighed. I'll do my best. It's your last meal. You deserve it, right? Thank you. He turned back. Your mom must have been something special. She was. She died five years ago. I'm sorry. Me too. But if I'm going to die Friday, I want to taste your cooking. One last time, the chef nodded. I'll make it exactly how you wrote it. The chef called the warden. Half these ingredients aren't in our inventory. I need to special order them. Suppliers can deliver Thursday morning, but this recipe takes eight hours minimum. The warden checked his watch. Execution is Friday at six PM you have time? Barely. Thursday morning, 8:00am, the ingredients arrived and the chef started cooking. I could smell it from my cell. An hour later, onions sauteing and butter. Mom's kitchen. Saturday mornings, her humming while she cooked. Sat on my bunk and cried. First time in eight years a guard walked by. You okay, Preston? Yeah. Just smells like home. Thursday afternoon, the chef ran into problems. The oven temperature wasn't holding steady. He had to recalibrate, start over on the glaze twice. It has to be perfect, he told the warden. It's his last meal. Thursday night, I couldn't sleep. Not from fear, from the smell, the meatloaf aching through the night. My lawyer stopped calling months ago. My appeals were done. My family stopped visiting two years ago. They believed I killed Rebecca. I was alone with this meatloaf and memories of my mother. Friday morning, execute Today, 10:00am. No meal yet. Noon, the chef. The glaze isn't right yet. Two PM, a guard brought regular lunch. Where's my last meal? Chef says it's not ready. Four hours left. Four PM, Two hours until they killed me. The smell was stronger. The Glaze caramelizing. Guards walked by to smell it. Five PM, One hour left, the warden came to my cell. Your meal isn't ready. We're delaying the execution two hours until eight PM six PM, the original execution time came and went. I was still alive waiting for meatloaf. It was absurd. I almost laughed. At least my mom's recipe was causing trouble. One last time. Seven PM, the smell was overwhelming, exactly like I remembered. Seven thirty PM, the chef appeared at my cell with a covered plate. He looked exhausted. I'm sorry it took so long. He uncovered it. The meatloaf looked exactly like my mother's. I ate slowly, savored every bite. It was perfect. Exactly like I remembered. The chef watched me eat. It's right. It's perfect. I finished the last bite at seven fifty one PM, Nine minutes left. The guard opened my cell. Time to go, Preston. They walked me down the hallway, past other cells. Inmates were silent. They always were during execution walks. We reached the preparation room. The chaplain was waiting. Mister Preston, would you like to pray? No.

La familia que antes era feliz se rompió de repente. Neeson, devastado, pensó en acabar con su vida, pero justo en ese momento, kevin, el compañero de su hijo, apareció. Le reveló la verdad a neeson. Resulta que unos días antes, kevin había visto a los gánsteres traficando y en su codicia, escondió una bolsa de drogas Esto desató la venganza de la banda. Justo ese día, el hijo de neeson estaba trabajando horas extras y fueron secuestrados por los gánsteres. Kevin aprovechó un momento para escapar saltando del coche, pero el hijo de nelson no tuvo la misma suerte. Después de ser brutalmente torturado, fue asesinado. Al saber la verdad, nelson estalló de ira pensando en el sufrimiento que su hijo había pasado antes de morir. Juró vengarse rápidamente. Gracias a la información de kevin, encontró a uno de los asesinos. Pero tan pronto como nelson habló, el hombre lo reconoció y trató de atacarlo con una pistola. Sin embargo, nelson reaccionó rápidamente y lo abatió de un disparo. Luego le exigió que le dijera quién mató a su hijo. El hombre, aterrorizado, confesó que su jefe era el hombre barbudo. Después de obtener lo que quería, neeson no dudó y lo mató de un tiro. Luego envolvió el cadáver en una red de alambre y lo arrojó al agua fría del río. Tras varios días esperando, neeson finalmente descubrió la ubicación del hombre barbudo. Lo interceptó y le dio un golpe. Pero este hombre también era duro. No solo no reveló quién estaba detrás de todo, sino que, furioso, maldijo a neeson al ver que no sacaría nada útil de él. Neeson lo mató de un disparo y lo envió al infierno. Sin pistas, neeson fue a ver a su hermano brock, quien estaba involucrado en el crimen organizado. Tras conocer toda la situación, brock Concluyó que los hombres que neeson había matado eran subordinados de un gánster conocido como viking, un hombre brutal y sanguinario que ya había matado a más de 10 personas. Matarlo no sería fácil. Para proteger a neeson, brock sugirió contratar a un asesino profesional. Neeson aceptó el consejo y contactó a un asesino pagándole 50.000 dólares para que matara a viking. Pero lo que neeson no sabía era que el asesino no tenía ética profesional. Después de recibir el dinero, vendió la información a viking por $100,000. Lo que el asesino no esperaba era que viking odiara profundamente a las personas sin ética profesional, así que inmediatamente hizo que alguien cerrara las cortinas y poco después el asesino fue sacado del lugar. Viking, siguiendo la pista, encontró a brock para proteger a su hermano. Brock confesó todo, incluyendo los asesinatos de los subordinados de viking. Así quería proteger a su hermano por última vez en el funeral de brock. Neeson estaba devastado. Juró encontrar a viking y vengar tanto a su hermano como a su hijo

Then she noticed a railway track nearby, the train thundering toward it. Looking at her own healthy legs, a dangerous thought struck her. If she placed the prosthetic on the track and let the train destroy it, it would appear her sister had no disability. With that evidence, no one would doubt the story. She carefully set the fake leg in the middle of the track, then hid behind a rock, holding her breath as she waited for the roar of steel.

voice_to_text: People often underestimate it, but even a single droplet of water can become a force of nature. Given enough time, drip after drip carved an entire cavern beneath the Simpsons property. The old foundation slowly hollowed out until the ground finally gave way. It all started with something small. Marge noticed their faucet leaking and asked Homer to take care of it. A year went by. Homer never touched it. By the time they realized how bad things were, the earth beneath their home had collapsed into a massive sinkhole. Totally unaware of the danger, Marge was getting ready to drive the kids to school. Bart was ecstatic. He smelled a chance to skip class. But Marge wasn't about to give him that victory. She popped open her emergency kit and deployed an inflatable escape ladder like it was standard procedure. News crews swarmed the scene and within hours the government rolled out an official solution, fill the sinkhole with whatever trash they could find before it grew any bigger. In the chaos, Marge's car got swallowed by the garbage heap. With the compensation money the city handed out, she purchased a shiny high tech replacement. But from the moment she sat inside, she sensed something strange, a weird odor no one else seemed to notice. I don't smell anything. Me neither. But the scent bothered her more by the minute. Trying to help, Homer grabbed a handful of gas station hot dogs to fix the smell, then lit a Cigarette on top of it, his idea of deodorizing. Marge still insisted something wasn't right, so they took the car to a mechanic. After a full checkup, the verdict was simple, nothing's wrong with it. But deep down, Marge knew this wasn't just about a smell, and the story was far from over.

voice_to_text: Every morning, the first thing he does is check whether his wife has finally passed away. But unfortunately for him, the 80 year old wealthy grandma is still breathing just fine today. He hung around fancy VIP clubs every single day. And on his 20th birthday, he finally spotted the perfect target. A buddy told him the wealthy woman was 55, recently divorced and had no children. voice_to_text: This woman wasn't visiting the butcher for dinner. She was preparing an escape. With a swift snap, she broke a steel saw blade in half and buried the pieces deep inside a pile of ground beef. After kneading it thoroughly, she wrapped the meat tight in plastic and left it to freeze overnight. The next morning at work, she casually slipped the frozen package to an inmate through a guard she happened to be friendly with. Mike didn't flinch. He unwrapped the package right under the guard's nose. Just be nothing more. Satisfied, the guard walked away. But the moment the coast was clear, Mike rushed to the sink, thawed the frozen meat under running water, and pulled out the saw blades hidden within. The escape had officially begun. Next, he tore toilet paper into strips, broke open an entire box of matches, wrapped them tight, and stuffed the makeshift fire bomb into an empty instant noodle bag. And he headed to the common area and signaled his partner on the upper floor as they passed each other on the stairs. The handoff was clean. Minutes later, while everyone else was distracted with activities, the accomplice slipped back to the cell and quietly lit a fire in the room next to Mike's. By the time the flames spread, the alarm was screaming through the block, and guards rushed in to extinguish the blaze. The wall was scorched black and would need repainting. Exactly as Mike planned. Back in the cell, Mike passed the saw fragments to John, the team's craftsmen. John wrapped cloth around both ends, snapped the blade again, then used a nail clipper, a rubber band, and layers of cloth to fashion two crude but effective saw handles. In minutes, two escape tools were ready. During the day, while most inmates were outside, the duo went to work. One posed as the guy repainting the smoke damaged wall, keeping watch, while the other slipped inside the empty cell, sawing through the ventilation grid inch by inch. Mike had even figured out in advance how to gather the falling metal dust without leaving a trace.

voice_to_text: This woman noticed a customer eating only the filling and leaving all the wrappers behind. She rushed over and asked what was wrong. The customer said the filling was amazing, but people here didn't like thick dumpling skins. Only then did she realize she had been using her hometown recipe, recipe that didn't match the taste of the locals. When she returned home, she began experimenting non stop. She rolled every wrapper 15 times until it became large, paper thin and nearly transparent. But when she returned to the market the next day, still no one bought a single dumpling. The stall beside hers was packed, while her booth stood completely empty. No matter how loud she shouted, no matter how hard she tried, no one stopped. By nightfall, the dumplings had lost their freshness. Holding back tears, she dumped the entire tray into the trash. Yet she refused to quit. She asked her landlord to try them, but he shook his head, saying they still weren't as thin as the wonton skins locals love. The next day, she carried her dumplings to a nearby wonton shop for advice. Shop owner nodded. The taste was good, but if she wanted the wrappers thin like real Hong Kong wontons, she would need alkaline water. She went home and immediately tested it. She added an entire bowl of alkaline water into the dough. Sure enough, the skins became thinner and larger. But the moment she took a bite, she spat it out. Bitterness Was overwhelming. Then she noticed salt sitting on the table. She added it to the flour and slowly mixed in alkaline water in small amounts until the flavor balanced perfectly. Last, she created the perfect thin wrapper. When she brought the improved dumplings back to the market, the locals love them. They sold out in no time. But her success drew unwanted attention. A local gang showed up demanding Protection, money, and even tried to take her daughter. She grabbed a kitchen knife and stood in front of her children ready to fight. The gang leader froze for a moment. He remembered his own mother standing in front of him the exact same way. Moved by her courage, he ordered a bowl of dumplings. She didn't want to serve him, but she did. After finishing, he kept praising the taste and even ordered dumplings for all his men. From then on, he never bothered her again. He even lowered the Protection fee. Before leaving, he placed an order for 500 dumplings. She finally smiled. Not only was the danger gone, she had just gained her biggest customer. That same night, someone asked to buy frozen dumplings to take home. At first, she refused, afraid they'd spoil. But the customer mentioned they had a freezer and that single sentence sparked an idea. From that day forward, she sold fresh dumplings and frozen ones.

voice_to_text: My parents were furious when they Learned we bought a new house and called a selfish. So my husband threw them out. But what they said next changed everything. My parents always treated me like the family servant, while my brother got everything. Growing up, I'd mow lawns while he played video games. I do laundry while he hung out with friends. When I complained, my dad would say I was being ungrateful. I left at 19 and never looked back. I met my wife in grad school. She saw how my family treated me and was horrified. When I told my parents we were getting engaged at 25, they said she was beneath me, that I was making a mistake. We got married anyway. Just her family there. They moved to Florida about eight years ago. Honestly, our relationship only works with distance. We text sometimes, but it's always tense. Last month, my wife and I bought our dream condo. Two bedrooms, downtown, everything we wanted. We were thrilled, but kept it quiet from my parents. They're paying for a storage unit nearby, and I knew exactly what would happen if they found out. As far as they knew, we rented a studio near my wife's office. Yesterday afternoon, I was working from home when my college buddy Ryan knocked. Behind him were my parents, running like they pulled off a surprise. Ryan ran into them at target and thought it'd be nice to bring them over. The moment They walked in and saw our open concept living room, the granite counters, the balcony view. My mom's smile died. She looked around slowly, face getting redder. Then she exploded. She screamed about how selfish we were. All this space and we never offered to help with. She yelled about how we've been getting along so well lately. Why would I lie? She said I was sneaky and ungrateful, just like always. I stood there frozen. Ryan looked horrified. My mom kept going. Family helps family. You clearly don't care about us. That's when my wife came home. She walked in, saw my mom gesturing wildly, saw my face, and her expression hardened. She set down her bag. Stop yelling in our home! My dad quiet until then. Face bright red. Your home? He spat. You mean the home my money helped buy? The room went silent. I felt my stomach drop. I turned to face my parents. What money? My mom's angry expression shifted to something smug. She crossed her arms. We've been sending your brother $1,500 every month for eight years to help you both. We assumed he was splitting it like we asked. My wife's jaw dropped. I couldn't breathe. Eight years, $1,500 a month? That's $144,000. My brother bought a boat last year. He went to Japan twice. He drives a Tesla. And I'm standing in my first home that we scraped together for learning. He pocketed money meant for both of us. My hands shook. As I called my brother on speaker, he answered, hey, what's up? Did mom and dad give you money for me? Long silence and quietly. They said it was for both of us to use however we needed. So you used it all? Another pause. I figured you were doing fine without it. My mom's smug look was racking. She was realizing what she just exposed. My dad looked between me and my wife, face pale now. I hung up. The room was so quiet, I could hear my heartbeat. My wife walked to the door and opened it wide. Her voice was ice. Get out the condo we bought with our own money. Don't come back. My mom tried to sputter about family, about misunderstandings. My wife just stood there, holding the door. My dad grabbed Mom's arm and pulled her out. As they left, my mom turned back. You'll regret this. My wife closed the door in her face. We stood in silence, and she hugged me. Ryan was sitting on the couch, stunned. I'm so sorry. I had no idea neither.

voice_to_text: I'm already 40 years old but still living off my parents and I have no intention of going out to make money. Every night I play games until the early morning, then sleep until noon the next day. I've been single all my life and still live with my parents. After eating, I go upstairs to my room and then stay there all day. I usually only go out late at night and only to the convenience store to buy instant noodles and drinks. I'm extremely socially anxious, afraid of talking to people. Even when I communicate with my parents, I do it through notes. One day when I got up for lunch, I saw a message from my mom on the lunch box. She said she wanted to remodel the house into a two family home. I kept wondering why. We were living just fine, so why change it? Suddenly, before I could figure it out, I heard a crowd of people outside the door. My social anxiety made me too scared to face them, so I grabbed my lunch box and hurried back to my room. It turned out my parents and my sister had arrived, along with a renovation company manager who brought the blueprints. My sister and her husband didn't want to rent anymore, so they planned to move back home with my parents during the remodel. While they were discussing the details, the manager suddenly said the house wouldn't be a standard two family design Since there was a single man in the family, it would be turned into a 2.5 unit home instead. Hearing that, my sister got upset. She complained that I was too old to still live at home, said I should move out and live independently. But my mom disagreed. She insisted that I stay there. It was a condition for the remodel. Seeing them about to argue, my brother in law stepped in and said he could give up his study room and that room could be used for me. So the renovation plan was decided. I had been eavesdropping on the whole thing, lying quietly on the floor listening. Then I suddenly heard the sound of children playing outside my door. My sister's two kids were running around upstairs. When I saw the doorknob turn, my nerves instantly tensed up. I hadn't seen my niece and nephew for years and I had no idea what to say to them. Finally, I gathered my courage and opened the door. But when I opened it, I saw Anna. It was my first time seeing her grown up. But she looked at me with disgust, calling me a creepy old man. I instantly felt a wave of regret. I should have just stayed hidden in my room. A few days later, the renovation began. The night before, I quietly moved out. At my usual convenience store, I bought a bunch of instant noodles, then dragged my luggage to an internet cafe. During My time as a shut in, I used to record my gaming videos and post them online because I was really good at gaming. I gained quite a few followers while chatting in game about my home situation. My gaming friends suggested I start streaming for money. They said with my skills, I could easily earn enough to move into a fancy apartment. I took their advice. The next day I started streaming without showing my face, but because it was my first time, I was too nervous and made a lot of mistakes. The viewers started insulting me in the chat, accusing me of being a fake skilled gamer. My first live stream ended in complete failure and my dream of moving into a luxury apartment came to an end.

voice_to_text: I had two knives bound to my arms, forcing me to walk with my arms outstretched. This was one of the Shaolin Temple's methods for building arm strength. But to earn my place at the Shaolin Temple and learn Kung fu, I had to pass this test of strength. After just one month, I could easily handle the water buckets and even help newcomer monks. My master was very pleased with me, but used my unauthorized assistance to others as reason to send me to train under another master. I arrived at the wrist training area. There the master instructed me to use one hand to hold a bamboo pole and lift a 10 pound iron hammer. I was to strike the bronze bell in the courtyard following the rhythm of the master's wooden fish drum. At first, I couldn't even lift the hammer. I moved forward to grasp the bamboo pole. As the master tapped the wooden fish, I attempted to strike the bronze bell. But before long my striking slowed down considerably. I could barely hold the bamboo pole. My senior brother Wouldn't allow me to stop, and I had no choice but to switch hands and continue training. Through sheer determination, I quickly discovered the secret. By focusing my power at the wrist, I could easily lift the hammer with a bamboo pole. As the master's drumming became faster, I still managed to keep pace. The master then directed me to the next room. There, I had to stand between two large incense sticks, following the master's candle movement with my eyes only. The master recognized my exceptional talent for martial arts and accepted me as a student.

This time, years of unfair treatment finally got to him, grabbed James by the neck and started choking him. He said he didn't know what came over him, but his mom screaming and beating couldn't stop him. He just saw red. He started yelling at James, demanding him to tell the truth. James Was struggling and begging Jack to release him. And finally, James admitted the truth. Jack let go. James was left gasping for air and Jack ran away straight to my apartment. After a while, my brother called to ask me to send Jack home because he had a lot to answer for. Jack wanted to return home to face the consequences alone, but I went with him. When we arrived, I saw James visibly.

video_description: My father tried to CANCEL my birthday trip because my golden child sister had a RUNNY NOSE...
voice_to_text: My nephew's golden child brother set him up and made his life miserable. So he taught him a lesson he would never forget. Jack was born when my brother was still in college. He didn't want a child at that time. He and his girlfriend struggled for a while managing their studies and raising a child. Thankfully, our parents were supportive and helped him. I also helped in any way I could. Eventually, he finished his studies, landed a job at 27 and married his girlfriend. Then their second child, James, was born. Both of them spoiled him a lot. Whenever our parents or I said anything, they claimed James was their planned child and since they were in a good position, James deserved it. The same time they neglected Jack. They gave James expensive gifts, toys, clothes, snacks and everything. The saddest part is that Jack never once complained. I watched that kid be happy just because his brother was happy opening his gifts. James, on the other hand, was spoiled rotten. He constantly compares his things to Jack's. And if Jack ever gets something good from someone, he wants it, too. This problem kept growing. The negligence towards Jack worsened and James started taking advantage of it. He began getting Jack grounded for things he did. And their parents always believed James no matter what. Over the years, I saw the sparkle in Jack's eyes fade. Now the incident happened this Christmas. To be clear, I love both Of my nephews. I don't approve of James's behavior, but I blame the parents, not the kid. So for Christmas, I bought both of them a Nintendo Switch. Jack had wanted one for years and almost cried when he got it. He hugged me and thanked me, but James hated it, saying I wanted a PS five, not this, and threw it away. I didn't care because I did my part. Whatever he did with his gift was none of my concerns. I was not going to enable this kid like his parents did. Few days after Christmas, Jack came knocking on my door. The kid was crying and shaking. I let him in, calmed him down and asked him what happened. To keep it short. After I gave them both a Nintendo Switch, Jack was too happy with it. He played The Legend of Zelda whenever he had time and had so much fun. That didn't sit well with James, ruined Jack's fun. James broke his console and cried to their mom, claiming that Jack had broken it. Their mom believed him, snatched Jack's console, gave it to James and grounded Jack. Jack just lost it. This time, years of unfair treatment finally got to him, grabbed James by the neck and started choking him. He said he didn't know what came over him, but his mom screaming and beating couldn't stop him. He just saw red. He started yelling at James, demanding him to tell the truth. James Was struggling and begging Jack to release him. And finally, James admitted the truth. Jack let go. James was left gasping for air and Jack ran away straight to my apartment. After a while, my brother called to ask me to send Jack home because he had a lot to answer for. Jack wanted to return home to face the consequences alone, but I went with him. When we arrived, I saw James.

video_description: My father tried to CANCEL my birthday trip because my golden child sister had a RUNNY NOSE...
voice_to_text: My father tried to cancel my birthday trip because my golden child sister had a runny nose. Years later, his worst fear came true. My father has always favored my sister. Not only does the family call him out on it, he admits to it. His defense is that my sister looks so much like our late mother that he can't help but spoil her. My sister caught onto this and used it to her advantage. If she wanted something from the store, she had to say please, dad, and he would get it for her. If I asked for something, my dad would ask me what I had done to deserve it. And if I couldn't think of something good I hadn't recently, I didn't get it. Never. My sister did something bad, she would begin to cry and dad would easily forgive her. If I did something bad, I always had to face the full consequences. Dad would leave work and get my sister from school for anything as small as a splinter. While I could be throwing up, dad would say he couldn't leave work and I had to tough it out. I tried hard to earn his love and attention, but nothing worked. I tried excelling at school, acting out and even forcing myself to get into his hobbies in hopes we would bond that way. The day I gave up was the day I found out how little my dad cared about me. I was Turning 15, the plan was for me, my dad, sister, uncle and two friends to go to an arcade two hours away. The day before my birthday, my sister got the sniffles. My dad could not travel and we would have to cancel the trip. I tried to convince him to leave her with our grandparents, but he didn't want to leave her to suffer alone. He told me to call my friends and tell them while he went and called my uncle. After he walked away, I went and cried my eyes out. About a gallon of tears later, I got a call from my uncle telling me not to worry. He would take us to the arcade. I had a great time and forgot all about my dad and sister. When I got back and my sister saw all my prizes, she asked if she could have one. I said, sorry, no, these are from my birthday trip. Later, my dad came to me and told me it would be nice if I gave my sister something, replied with something along the lines of, you know what would be nice if you didn't try to cancel my birthday over my sister's runny nose. My dad called me selfish and said my sister's health was more important and I would be a good big brother if I gave her something. I didn't give her anything. After that incident, I gave up on my father. I focused on those who Cared for me. My father either didn't notice or didn't care. As long as he had my sister, that's all he needed. He didn't start caring until it made him look bad in the public eye. During my senior year, the band had an award ceremony. I didn't even bother asking my dad to attend. Instead, I asked my aunt and uncle. My dad didn't notice until he saw the family post on Facebook in the school. Any of the comments on the post asked why my dad wasn't there. He confronted me and asked why I hadn't told him he would have loved to go. I replied that in all the years of me winning awards, you've never shown up to support me. Why would I expect you to start now? Later, I Learned from my cousin that my dad had called my uncle to fuss at him for taking.

part2 My family ignored me becoming a lawyer then my brother got arrested and suddenly they needed me.#ask#askreddit#LearnOnTikTok#reddit#satisfying
voice_to_text: Didn't respond. My mom called once and said, your father is hurt, that you won't come around anymore. Family is supposed to forgive. I said, family is supposed to show up, and hung up. Six months after my swearing in ceremony, I got a call from my dad at 2 in the morning. He said, Silas has been arrested. You need to come to the police station right now. I was exhausted from a long day in court, but I got dressed and drove 40 minutes to the state. Silas had gotten into a bar fight and assaulted someone badly enough to send them to the hospital. The charges were aggravated assault, and he was looking at serious prison time. My dad grabbed my arm when I walked in and said, you have to fix this. You're a lawyer. You can make this go away. I said, I'm a criminal defense attorney. I don't make things go away. I defend people in court. He said, so defend him. He's your brother. I looked at Silas sitting in the holding cell, and he wouldn't even look at me. My dad said, we're family. You owe us this. I said, I owe you this. Where were you six months ago when I got sworn in? My dad said, this is different. This is important. That was just a ceremony. I felt something cold settle in my chest and said, you want me to represent Silas? He said, of course. You're his brother. I said, my hourly rate is $500 dollars. A case like this will probably cost around 50,000 by the time we get to trial. My dad's face went red and he said, you're going to charge your own brother? I said, you're asking me to use the law degree you said wasn't a big deal? The one you couldn't be bothered to celebrate? Yeah, I'm going to charge him. My dad said, how can you be so selfish? He's family. I said, family shows up. You didn't show up for me. Why should I show up for him? Alice finally spoke up and said, come on, you know I didn't mean anything by missing your thing. This is my life we're talking about. I said, it was my life too. I worked for years to get that degree. I sacrificed everything. And when I finally succeeded, you chose a golf tournament over being there. My dad said, we'll pay whatever you want, just please help him. I said, I'll represent him. Standard rates, 50% up front. And I want you all to know that every single hour I Bill is an hour you told me wasn't worth your time. I got Silas a plea deal that kept him out of prison. They paid every invoice on time. We haven't spoken since.

video_description: My family ignored me becoming a lawyer then my brother got arrested and suddenly they needed me.
voice_to_text: My family didn't care when I became a lawyer until my brother got arrested. Then all of a sudden they wanted me again. After I passed the bar exam to become a lawyer. I texted my family the date and time of my swearing and ceremony. My dad replied saying he couldn't make it because my brother Silas had a golf tournament at the same day. My mom said she'd be at the tournament too. Silas sent a laughing emoji and wrote, it's just a ceremony. You already passed. We'll celebrate later. I stared at my phone and typed back, understood. The ceremony was beautiful and I sat there in a room full of new lawyers with their families cheering and taking pictures. I was alone. The woman next to me had her entire extended family there and they kept apologizing for being too loud. I told them it was fine and tried not to cry. Afterwards, the law firm I joined took photos of all the new associates for their website and newsletter. I smiled in my professional headshot and pretended I wasn't heartbroken. My boss pulled me aside and said, where's your family? I wanted to meet them. I said they couldn't make it. And he looked confused but didn't push. I started working criminal defense and I was good at it, really good. I won cases that senior partners said were unwinnable. I worked 80 hour weeks and built a reputation. My family never asked about my Work. At Thanksgiving, my dad spent an hour talking about Silas's promotion at his sales job. And when I mentioned I'd won a major case, he said, that's nice and change the object. Silas asked if I was dating anyone. And when I said I was too busy with work, he said, you're always going to be too busy. That's your problem. My mom nodded and said, he's right. You need balance. I said, I have balance. I'm building a career. My dad laughed and said, Silas has a career and still makes time for family. Maybe you should take notes. On Christmas, my dad gave Silas an expensive watch and gave me a gift card to target. When I opened it, Silas smirked and said, at least you can buy yourself something nice. I left early and my mom texted me later saying I'd ruined Christmas by being dramatic. I stopped going to family dinners. After that, my dad would text saying I was being distant and I needed to make more effort. Didn't respond. My mom called once and said, your father is hurt that you won't come around anymore. Haley and I were having relationship issues, and I felt she was looking for an excuse to leave me. Because of my leg condition, this move felt like a cover for breaking up with me. The more I thought about it, the angrier I became, and I decided to chase the hacker down. On the way, he sent us Traffic camera photos of our car taunting us. Using the GPS coordinates, we tracked down a small cabin. Jonah and I went inside to investigate, recording everything as we searched. Suddenly, Haley, who had stayed outside, let out a scream. When I ran out, I saw her being lifted into the air. A blinding white light hit me, and I instantly blacked out. I don't know how long I was unconscious, but when I woke up, I was sitting in a wheelchair, completely unable to move. In front of me sat a man in a hazmat suit named Wallace, who claimed he would help me recover my memory. He told me we had come into contact with extraterrestrial life forms and had likely been contaminated. As he spoke, black blood began dripping from my nose. After examining me, Wallace ordered his team to return me to the isolation room. The next day, they brought me back to that same room again.

voice_to_text: Este gato era considerado tan feo. Cada cliente que lo veía movía la cabeza y se marchaba. Incluso cuando su precio se redujo al mínimo, nadie estaba dispuesto a mirarlo siquiera. El gato comenzó a creer que nadie en el mundo lo querría. Dejó de comer su comida para gatos, miraba con desesperación a otros gatos ser adoptados y mimados. Un día, un hombre entró en la tienda de mascotas. El empleado le presentó ansiosamente a este gato porque pronto cumpliría un año y ahora nadie quería comprar un gato adulto. Si para ese momento sigue sin que nadie lo compre, lo tendrían que enviar a un refugio oscuro y pequeño. Pero su entusiasmo era tan abrumador que accidentalmente asustaron al hombre. El gato pensara, claro que nadie me quiere. Mientras el empleado se preocupaba por el futuro del gato, encontraron un collar en la entrada de la tienda, dos anillos colgando de él. Poco después el hombre regresó para buscar el collar. Resultó que el hombre extrañaba mucho a su esposa, por eso había colgado los anillos de boda en un collar para llevarlos y había venido a la tienda de mascotas porque de repente recordó que cuando su esposa estaba viva quería tener un gato. Mientras tanto, el gato pensaba que si fuera ese collar, quizás también podría ser apreciado por alguien. Mientras el hombre se disponía a ponerse el collar, un cachorro ladró de repente, asustándolo tanto que dejó caer el anillo y el anillo rodó directamente Hacia el gato. Cuando el hombre se agachó para recogerlo, él y el gato levantaron la cabeza al mismo tiempo. Sus miradas se cruzaron. El hombre miró fijamente al gato y el gato le devolvió la mirada. Así, sin más, el hombre decidió adoptar al gato. Tanto el empleado como el gato estaban sorprendidos. El gato no podía creer que alguien lo quisiera, pero el hombre pensaba que ese gato tan feo era absolutamente adorable y el gato disfrutaba del calor en sus brazos. No podía creer que esto estuviera pasando de verdad. Al ver que el gato había encontrado un dueño, el personal se alegró de verdad por él. El hombre se llevó al gato a casa, pero este tenía demasiado miedo para salir de su transportín, por si a la familia del hombre tampoco le gustaría. Entonces el hombre le dijo, al gato vivo solo aquí. Entonces el gato entendió que este hombre estaba tan solo como él, así que salió lentamente de la caja. Se acercó al hombre para consolarlo. El hombre empezó a decirle un montón de nombres al gato, lo que lo confundió por completo hasta que entendió que el hombre le estaba eligiendo un nombre. Finalmente, el hombre decidió llamar al gato Shang Chain, porque conocer a este gato le había devuelto la calidez a su vida. Pero era la primera vez que él tenía un gato y no tenía ni idea de cuánta arena debía usar, así que por seguridad echó una Bolsa entera también midió cuidadosamente la comida del gato. El gato perezoso comió su comida y volvió directamente a su caja para dormir. Al ver al gato dormir tan plácidamente, el hombre pensó en su difunta esposa. Ahora él también tenía un gato, pero por desgracia su esposa nunca lo vería. Cuando el hombre se acostó para dormir, se metió lentamente en la manta hasta llegar al lado de él. Tratando de consolar al hombre afligido, él abrazó suavemente al gato. Pronto, tanto el hombre como el gato se quedaron dormidos. El hombre nunca esperó que tras el fallecimiento de su esposa, esta sería la primera vez que dormiría tan profundamente. Todo gracias a este adorable gato que le devolvió la calidez y la esperanza a su vida. Y el gato finalmente encontró un lugar que realmente podía llamar hogar

El lugar estaba fuertemente custodiado por militares y policías. La caballería rodeaba todo el sitio. Había francotiradores en los techos, incluso aviones y tanques patrullaban la zona. La seguridad era extrema, pero el presidente aún no había llegado. El asesino sacó las piezas del arma escondidas en su bastón y con movimientos hábiles montó un rifle francotirador improvisado. Después colocó una silla sobre la mesa, apoyó el arma y esperó en silencio la llegada del presidente. El asesino se llamaba ben. Nunca había fallado en su carrera. Cuando supo que su objetivo era el presidente, pidió 3000000 de libras y la mitad por adelantado. El líder rebelde aceptó tras discutirlo con su equipo. Al día siguiente, ben comenzó a ejecutar su plan. Primero fue al cementerio y encontró un cadáver con un rostro parecido al suyo. Luego se hizo pasar por familiar del difunto para obtener su información y usó esa identidad para falsificar documentos como el pasaporte y la identificación. A la mañana siguiente, visitó a un viejo amigo y le pidió un rifle francotirador. Simple pero letal, liviano, fácil de transportar, con silenciador y un alcance de 500 pies, su Amigo construyó el arma según sus especificaciones. Era ligera, fácil de armar y casi sin retroceso. Al disparar, ben quedó satisfecho y ansioso por probar su potencia. Condujo hasta un campo apartado, colgó una sandía a unos 600m de un árbol, dibujó un blanco sobre ella y se preparó para disparar. Ajustó la mira y apuntó directamente al presidente.

voice_to_text: La niña se escondió debajo de la cama y tembló un pie con 10 dedos bajó de un salto, se movió lentamente y empezó a buscar a la niña. La niña contuvo la respiración sin atreverse a moverse. En ese momento, el monstruo rugió. Parecía estar llamando a sus compañeros. La niña pensó que esta vez estaba muerta, pero el monstruo se volvió hacia la ventana. Luego desapareció. En la noche. La muchacha se atrevió a soltar un largo suspiro. Se apresuró a cerrar la ventana del dormitorio, luego se dirigió en silencio al salón con la intención de cerrar también la puerta de la casa. De repente, se oyó un ruido extraño procedente del tejado. Annie sintió que el corazón le latía en la garganta una vez más. Solo pudo acelerar el paso y apresurarse a bajar las escaleras. Pensó que estaba a salvo cuando cerró la puerta, pero de repente todos los aparatos se encendieron y apagaron y emitieron un sonido desgarrador. Se apresuró a desenchufar la fuente de alimentación y finalmente todo volvió a la calma. Annie cogió el teléfono para llamar a la policía, pero el sonido penetrante comenzó de nuevo y la nevera se puso espeluznante. Peor aún, el monstruo había bloqueado las escaleras. Ella se retiró a la cocina y se escondió en un rincón. El teléfono también estaba colgado por el monstruo. La respiración acelerada seguía dejándola al descubierto. El refrigerador fue controlado de nuevo, atrapándola directamente dentro. El monstruo se acercaba. Paso A paso, Annie finalmente vio su verdadero rostro. Era en realidad un alienígena con grandes ojos. Annie gritó y empujó al monstruo. Entonces, Annie corrió hacia la puerta, pero el monstruo tomó el control de la puerta de la habitación. La chica fue noqueada. Al instante, Annie se despertó y se retorció apresuradamente dentro, pero su cuerpo estaba fuera de control. Presa del pánico, agarró un objeto puntiagudo accidentalmente se clavó en la cabeza del alienígena. El alien murió instantáneamente. Annie se desmayó por el shock. Despertó al día siguiente. Mirando al alien en el suelo, Annie se dio cuenta de que todo lo de anoche era real. Cogió un trozo de tela para cubrir al alienígena. Luego quiso llamar a la policía, pero el teléfono de su casa ya no funcionaba y todos los aparatos eléctricos habían perdido sus funciones. Aparentemente, el alienígena podía controlar objetos cargados eléctricamente. Annie decidió salir a buscar ayuda, pero extrañamente no había nadie en la carretera. Una ambulancia volcó en la carretera. Las casas cercanas también fueron atacadas. Ella no fue la única que se encontró con alienígenas anoche. Justo en ese momento, enormes nubes oscuras comenzaron a envolver el pueblo y siguieron acercándose a la ubicación de Annie. Ella tuvo que correr en dirección a su casa. En el camino, vio a sus vecinos que habían desaparecido. Extrañamente, estaban reunidos con sus manos derechas levantadas y con la mirada perdida en las nubes oscuras. Parecía muy espeluznante y algo parecía retorcerse en Sus gargantas y entonces un hombre vio a Annie. Ella no se atrevió a quedarse un momento y salió corriendo. La nube oscura se acercaba cada vez más. Annie estaba segura de que los alienígenas vendrían a vengarse, así que ajustó su mente y sacó su encendedor y encendió velas para iluminar la casa y hirvió 4 ollas de agua hirviendo. Estaba preparada para luchar a muerte contra los alienígenas
